&lt;p&gt;Points: 3&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47805251</guid><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 12:35:56 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Show HN: Mabon – AI agent that finds jobs continuously and shows strong matches</title><link>https://mabon.ai/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hey HN&lt;p&gt;I'd love to get your feedback on Mabon.ai.&lt;p&gt;I think job search is quite tedious for most people. They scan or subscribe to multiple job boards that often send jobs based on just a few keywords, without actually understanding the user's intent or what kind of job they 'really' want. Most of these job boards also seem to optimize for sending a high volume of matches rather than being targeted.&lt;p&gt;Mabon first understands the user's background and preferences, and then finds only relevant jobs specific to them.&lt;p&gt;Users can write anything they want in the preferences - "no consulting companies; only funded startups; salary at least $XXX", etc. After the search, it rates all the openings internally based on the user's profile &amp; preferences, and then shows only the strong matches.&lt;p&gt;Users can then converse with the agent to further refine the search, and once they think the agent has nailed it down, they can set the search to "always-on", so that it keeps scanning continuously.&lt;p&gt;It helps both active job seekers and folks who are selectively open to a real high-quality match when it shows up.&lt;p&gt;Btw, it is not limited to the tech sector; it's meant to work across different types of jobs and industries.&lt;p&gt;I put this into production just a few days ago, so it could be a bit rough around the edges. Please try it out and share your thoughts on it. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comments URL: &lt;a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47805227"&gt;https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47805227&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
